"There should be an elementary school on the edge of town."[p]
Cybil followed her intuition and decided that Cheryl probably headed for the school after wandering around town.[p]
Per her training in child psychology, she has learned that if a child loses their parents or guardian, [p]
then the chance is high that they will be drawn to places that they are most used to going, [p]
places where there are a lot of people.[p]
However, ahead of her all knowledge, either a bit instinctively, or due to a sense similar that to that of a memory coming back, [p]
she believed somewhere within her heart that Cheryl was probably at the elementary school.[p]


