Cybil opened a door leading to a long hallway. [p]
She looked through the glass windows placed in the doors of the classrooms while slowly walking.[p]
There was no sign of Cheryl.[p]
The courtyard is to her right.[p]
The landscaping is very nice, and has been well cared for.[p]
The snow has become sleet.[p]
It does not look like it will accumulate.[p]
In the back of the courtyard there is an old-feeling clock tower; however, Cybil is not particularly interested in it.[p]
"Hmm, I wonder how Harry is doing...[p]
I wonder if the gun I gave him has come in handy...[p]
If I cannot meet with Harry after I find Cheryl then it will be meaningless...[p]
We should have made plans to rendezvous somewhere..."[p]
Cybil thought this, but at this point nothing could be done.[p]


