"Perhaps I am just dreaming all of this?", Cybil thought.[p]
It is difficult for a person to tell whether they are dreaming or not while in a dream, [p]
but for her to accept these conditions is just as difficult.[p]
She has no memory of how she got to this town, so it seemed natural for her to think that she has been in a deep sleep, [p]
since the moment of the motorcycle accident until now.[p]
"Or possibly from even before then...[p]
From the time of the phone call with the Silent Hill police station?[p]
Or maybe..."[p]
While contemplating the many possibilities, Cybil climbed the stairs to the second floor of the school.[p]


